    "description": [
        {
            "text": "Mole per cubic metre hour is a unit of catalytic activity concentration, expressing amount of substance per unit volume per unit time with time measured in hours. It corresponds to the prefixed form \"nmol/(cm³·h)\" with the Nano (on mole) and Centi (on metre) prefixes removed; the resulting factor units are mol, m³, and h. Typical uses include reporting reaction or enzyme rates normalized by volume over hours.",
